So how would you characterize and define the tone of the above statement?  He made MANY comments like this, and I just called a spade a spade.  Are comments like &quot;get off our server&quot; constructive?  Are the targets of comments like that just supposed to comply without voicing their thoughts and opinions?<br>
<br>
Now it's interesting that you are using these types of examples to twist my comments into personal attacks.  You just stated:<br>
<br>
&quot;This is just a personal attack, again. It adds nothing substantial to the argument, and it attacks Shintou's character, not his argument. It implies that he's got a psychological problem, and that's why he disagrees with you. It's also an attempt to position yourself above Shintou: &quot;I'm normal, Shintou's sociopathic.&quot;<br>
<br>
Okay, so by the virtue of your arguement, let's examine one of your quotes:<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showMessageRange?topicID=229.topic&start=21&stop=40">pub94.ezboard.com/ffirion...21&stop=40</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--><br>
<br>
&quot;There is an underlying belief in the U.S. that &quot;freedom&quot; means freedom from social pressure to conform, and that any discursive regime that enforces social behavior is inherently evil, and I suspect your analysis of Shintou's opinion as being comparable to racism stems from this kind of thinking.&quot;<br>
<br>
Were you not using exactly the same tactic that you just rebuked, to discredit other points of views within that thread?  You gave an example of a line of thought that you hold to be flawed, and then drew a parallel between that example and the arguements that you wished to attack, thereby attempting to discredit the authors and thus all of their &quot;thinking&quot;.  This then places you upon a plateau of &quot;enlightened&quot; thinking untainted by the flawed rationalizations you just used to brand those you disagreed with.<br>
<br>
At any rate, to anyone who reads those threads, it should be clear that the majority of us were simply asking for a bit more tolerance and less ranting.  Unfortunately, some people became very defensive (which is somewhat understandable in the face of &quot;Get off our server&quot;) or tired of the endless rants and resorted to the personal comments.<br>
